{"$schema":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/oasis-tcs/sarif-spec/master/Schemata/sarif-schema-2.1.0.json","version":"2.1.0","runs":[{"tool":{"driver":{"name":"Checkmarx One","version":"1.0","informationUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","rules":[{"id":"SQL Injection - 14517067005933136034 (sast)","name":"SQL Injection","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with getValue, at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getValue; this input is then read by the  method at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n","markdown":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with getValue, at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getValue; this input is then read by the  method at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with getValue, at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getValue; this input is then read by the  method at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"9.0","name":"SQL Injection","id":"SQL Injection - 14517067005933136034 (sast)","description":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with getValue, at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nAn attacker would be able to inject arbitrary syntax and data into the SQL query, by crafting a malicious payload and providing it via the input getValue; this input is then read by the  method at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code, into a query and to the database server - without sanitization.\r\n\r\nThis may enable an SQL Injection attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Second Order SQL Injection - 8558184832467657344 (sast)","name":"Second Order SQL Injection","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with BinaryExpr, at line 14 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/Messages.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nThe attacker may be able to write arbitrary data to the database, which is then retrieved by the application with rs in  method at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/admin/adminlogin.jsp. This data then flows through the code, until it is used directly in the SQL query without sanitization, and then submitted to the database server for execution.\r\n\r\nThis may enable a Second-Order SQL Injection attack.\n\n","markdown":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with BinaryExpr, at line 14 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/Messages.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nThe attacker may be able to write arbitrary data to the database, which is then retrieved by the application with rs in  method at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/admin/adminlogin.jsp. This data then flows through the code, until it is used directly in the SQL query without sanitization, and then submitted to the database server for execution.\r\n\r\nThis may enable a Second-Order SQL Injection attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with BinaryExpr, at line 14 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/Messages.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nThe attacker may be able to write arbitrary data to the database, which is then retrieved by the application with rs in  method at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/admin/adminlogin.jsp. This data then flows through the code, until it is used directly in the SQL query without sanitization, and then submitted to the database server for execution.\r\n\r\nThis may enable a Second-Order SQL Injection attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"9.0","name":"Second Order SQL Injection","id":"Second Order SQL Injection - 8558184832467657344 (sast)","description":"The application\u0026#39;s  method executes an SQL query with BinaryExpr, at line 14 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/Messages.jsp. The application constructs this SQL query by embedding an untrusted string into the query without proper sanitization. The concatenated string is submitted to the database, where it is parsed and executed accordingly.\n\nThe attacker may be able to write arbitrary data to the database, which is then retrieved by the application with rs in  method at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/admin/adminlogin.jsp. This data then flows through the code, until it is used directly in the SQL query without sanitization, and then submitted to the database server for execution.\r\n\r\nThis may enable a Second-Order SQL Injection attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection') - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"9.0","name":"Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')","id":"Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection') - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Stored XSS - 13625251660291496964 (sast)","name":"Stored XSS","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with print, at line 24 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by saving malicious data in a data-store ahead of time. The attacker\u0026#39;s modified data is then read from the database by the  method with rs, at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","markdown":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with print, at line 24 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by saving malicious data in a data-store ahead of time. The attacker\u0026#39;s modified data is then read from the database by the  method with rs, at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with print, at line 24 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by saving malicious data in a data-store ahead of time. The attacker\u0026#39;s modified data is then read from the database by the  method with rs, at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"9.0","name":"Stored XSS","id":"Stored XSS - 13625251660291496964 (sast)","description":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with print, at line 24 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by saving malicious data in a data-store ahead of time. The attacker\u0026#39;s modified data is then read from the database by the  method with rs, at line 19 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/securitymisconfig/pages.jsp. This untrusted data then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference (XXE) - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference (XXE)","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference (XXE)","id":"Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference (XXE) - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) - 0 (sast)","name":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)","id":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Reflected XSS - 8481125285487743346 (sast)","name":"Reflected XSS","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with password, at line 23 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input getCookies, which is read by the  method at line 7 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","markdown":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with password, at line 23 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input getCookies, which is read by the  method at line 7 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with password, at line 23 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input getCookies, which is read by the  method at line 7 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Reflected XSS","id":"Reflected XSS - 8481125285487743346 (sast)","description":"The method  embeds untrusted data in generated output with password, at line 23 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This untrusted data is embedded into the output without proper sanitization or encoding, enabling an attacker to inject malicious code into the generated web-page.\n\nThe attacker would be able to alter the returned web page by simply providing modified data in the user input getCookies, which is read by the  method at line 7 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp. This input then flows through the code straight to the output web page, without sanitization. \r\n\r\nThis can enable a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2023-22102 (sca)","name":"Cve202322102","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). The affected versions are through 8.1.0. The difficult-to-exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attackers with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors.  Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products (scope change). Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. ","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). The affected versions are through 8.1.0. The difficult-to-exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attackers with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors.  Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products (scope change). Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. "},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). The affected versions are through 8.1.0. The difficult-to-exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attackers with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors.  Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products (scope change). Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. "},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202322102","id":"CVE-2023-22102 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). The affected versions are through 8.1.0. The difficult-to-exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attackers with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors.  Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products (scope change). Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. ","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2020-10683 (sca)","name":"Cve202010683","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"dom4j before 2.1.3 allows external DTDs and External Entities by default, which might enable XXE attacks. However, there is popular external documentation from OWASP showing how to enable the safe, non-default behavior in any application that uses dom4j.","markdown":"dom4j before 2.1.3 allows external DTDs and External Entities by default, which might enable XXE attacks. However, there is popular external documentation from OWASP showing how to enable the safe, non-default behavior in any application that uses dom4j."},"fullDescription":{"text":"dom4j before 2.1.3 allows external DTDs and External Entities by default, which might enable XXE attacks. However, there is popular external documentation from OWASP showing how to enable the safe, non-default behavior in any application that uses dom4j."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202010683","id":"CVE-2020-10683 (sca)","description":"dom4j before 2.1.3 allows external DTDs and External Entities by default, which might enable XXE attacks. However, there is popular external documentation from OWASP showing how to enable the safe, non-default behavior in any application that uses dom4j.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting') - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","id":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting') - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2022-45688 (sca)","name":"Cve202245688","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;XML.toJSONObject\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20230227, and \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.25.","markdown":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;XML.toJSONObject\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20230227, and \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.25."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;XML.toJSONObject\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20230227, and \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.25."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202245688","id":"CVE-2022-45688 (sca)","description":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;XML.toJSONObject\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20230227, and \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.25.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Cx039cb67c-ead3 (sca)","name":"Cx039cb67cead3","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.37 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. The method methodCompressedInputStream.getNextPacketFromServer() of src/com/mysq/jdbc/CompressedInputStream.java has high memory and garbage collection usage caused by the consecutive instantiation of a new inflater.","markdown":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.37 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. The method methodCompressedInputStream.getNextPacketFromServer() of src/com/mysq/jdbc/CompressedInputStream.java has high memory and garbage collection usage caused by the consecutive instantiation of a new inflater."},"fullDescription":{"text":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.37 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. The method methodCompressedInputStream.getNextPacketFromServer() of src/com/mysq/jdbc/CompressedInputStream.java has high memory and garbage collection usage caused by the consecutive instantiation of a new inflater."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cx039cb67cead3","id":"Cx039cb67c-ead3 (sca)","description":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.37 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. The method methodCompressedInputStream.getNextPacketFromServer() of src/com/mysq/jdbc/CompressedInputStream.java has high memory and garbage collection usage caused by the consecutive instantiation of a new inflater.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2023-5072 (sca)","name":"Cve20235072","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Denial of Service (DoS) in JSON-Java in versions prior to 20231013. A bug in the parser means that an input string of modest size can lead to indefinite amounts of memory being used.","markdown":"Denial of Service (DoS) in JSON-Java in versions prior to 20231013. A bug in the parser means that an input string of modest size can lead to indefinite amounts of memory being used."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Denial of Service (DoS) in JSON-Java in versions prior to 20231013. A bug in the parser means that an input string of modest size can lead to indefinite amounts of memory being used."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20235072","id":"CVE-2023-5072 (sca)","description":"Denial of Service (DoS) in JSON-Java in versions prior to 20231013. A bug in the parser means that an input string of modest size can lead to indefinite amounts of memory being used.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Relative Path Traversal - 11267356716587554023 (sast)","name":"Relative Path Traversal","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method  at line 18 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp gets dynamic data from the \u0026#34;\u0026#34;fileid\u0026#34;\u0026#34; element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in  at line 32 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n","markdown":"Method  at line 18 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp gets dynamic data from the \u0026#34;\u0026#34;fileid\u0026#34;\u0026#34; element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in  at line 32 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method  at line 18 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp gets dynamic data from the \u0026#34;\u0026#34;fileid\u0026#34;\u0026#34; element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in  at line 32 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Relative Path Traversal","id":"Relative Path Traversal - 11267356716587554023 (sast)","description":"Method  at line 18 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp gets dynamic data from the \u0026#34;\u0026#34;fileid\u0026#34;\u0026#34; element. This element’s value then flows through the code and is eventually used in a file path for local disk access in  at line 32 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/sqli/download_id.jsp. This may cause a Path Traversal vulnerability.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Connection String Injection - 16285059105102556494 (sast)","name":"Connection String Injection","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method receives untrusted, user-controlled data, and uses this data to connect to a database using BinaryExpr, at line 121 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java. This may enable a Connection String Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker can inject the connection string via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dburl\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 54 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java.\n\n","markdown":"The application\u0026#39;s  method receives untrusted, user-controlled data, and uses this data to connect to a database using BinaryExpr, at line 121 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java. This may enable a Connection String Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker can inject the connection string via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dburl\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 54 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method receives untrusted, user-controlled data, and uses this data to connect to a database using BinaryExpr, at line 121 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java. This may enable a Connection String Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker can inject the connection string via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dburl\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 54 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Connection String Injection","id":"Connection String Injection - 16285059105102556494 (sast)","description":"The application\u0026#39;s  method receives untrusted, user-controlled data, and uses this data to connect to a database using BinaryExpr, at line 121 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java. This may enable a Connection String Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker can inject the connection string via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dburl\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 54 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"SSRF - 15179929566605030594 (sast)","name":"SSRF","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The application sends a request to a remote server, for some resource, using BinaryExpr in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:121. However, an attacker can control the target of the request, by sending a URL or other data in \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34; at /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:58.\n\n","markdown":"The application sends a request to a remote server, for some resource, using BinaryExpr in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:121. However, an attacker can control the target of the request, by sending a URL or other data in \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34; at /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:58.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application sends a request to a remote server, for some resource, using BinaryExpr in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:121. However, an attacker can control the target of the request, by sending a URL or other data in \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34; at /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:58.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"SSRF","id":"SSRF - 15179929566605030594 (sast)","description":"The application sends a request to a remote server, for some resource, using BinaryExpr in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:121. However, an attacker can control the target of the request, by sending a URL or other data in \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34; at /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java:58.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Improper Neutralization of Data within XPath Expressions ('XPath Injection') - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Neutralization of Data within XPath Expressions ('XPath Injection')","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Neutralization of Data within XPath Expressions ('XPath Injection')","id":"Improper Neutralization of Data within XPath Expressions ('XPath Injection') - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2016-2170 (sca)","name":"Cve20162170","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Apache OFBiz 12.04.x before 12.04.06 and 13.07.x before 13.07.03 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0.","markdown":"Apache OFBiz 12.04.x before 12.04.06 and 13.07.x before 13.07.03 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Apache OFBiz 12.04.x before 12.04.06 and 13.07.x before 13.07.03 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20162170","id":"CVE-2016-2170 (sca)","description":"Apache OFBiz 12.04.x before 12.04.06 and 13.07.x before 13.07.03 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2015-2575 (sca)","name":"Cve20152575","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Improper Access Control vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component in Oracle MySQL versions prior to 5.1.35 allows remote authenticated users to affect confidentiality and integrity via unknown vectors related to Connector/J.","markdown":"Improper Access Control vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component in Oracle MySQL versions prior to 5.1.35 allows remote authenticated users to affect confidentiality and integrity via unknown vectors related to Connector/J."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Improper Access Control vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component in Oracle MySQL versions prior to 5.1.35 allows remote authenticated users to affect confidentiality and integrity via unknown vectors related to Connector/J."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20152575","id":"CVE-2015-2575 (sca)","description":"Improper Access Control vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component in Oracle MySQL versions prior to 5.1.35 allows remote authenticated users to affect confidentiality and integrity via unknown vectors related to Connector/J.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Cx2906ba70-607a (sca)","name":"Cx2906ba70607a","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The package `JSON-java` before 20171018 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service attack. The function `unescape()` used in multiple java files,  unescapes a given XML string twice, causing the application to crash, due to `StringIndexOutOfBoundsException`.","markdown":"The package `JSON-java` before 20171018 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service attack. The function `unescape()` used in multiple java files,  unescapes a given XML string twice, causing the application to crash, due to `StringIndexOutOfBoundsException`."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The package `JSON-java` before 20171018 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service attack. The function `unescape()` used in multiple java files,  unescapes a given XML string twice, causing the application to crash, due to `StringIndexOutOfBoundsException`."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cx2906ba70607a","id":"Cx2906ba70-607a (sca)","description":"The package `JSON-java` before 20171018 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service attack. The function `unescape()` used in multiple java files,  unescapes a given XML string twice, causing the application to crash, due to `StringIndexOutOfBoundsException`.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Cx7ef609d2-efb5 (sca)","name":"Cx7ef609d2efb5","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.31 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. Upon continuous interruption between the server and the database, the dead connections are accumulated in a map in `ProfilerEventHandlerFactory` factory  and aren\u0026#39;t removed from the memory. When the number of database connections reaches a certain number, it causes the application to throw an OutOfMemoryException as the garbage collector fails to collect the dead connections.","markdown":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.31 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. Upon continuous interruption between the server and the database, the dead connections are accumulated in a map in `ProfilerEventHandlerFactory` factory  and aren\u0026#39;t removed from the memory. When the number of database connections reaches a certain number, it causes the application to throw an OutOfMemoryException as the garbage collector fails to collect the dead connections."},"fullDescription":{"text":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.31 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. Upon continuous interruption between the server and the database, the dead connections are accumulated in a map in `ProfilerEventHandlerFactory` factory  and aren\u0026#39;t removed from the memory. When the number of database connections reaches a certain number, it causes the application to throw an OutOfMemoryException as the garbage collector fails to collect the dead connections."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cx7ef609d2efb5","id":"Cx7ef609d2-efb5 (sca)","description":"MySQL Connector/J before 5.1.31 is vulnerable to Memory Leak. Upon continuous interruption between the server and the database, the dead connections are accumulated in a map in `ProfilerEventHandlerFactory` factory  and aren\u0026#39;t removed from the memory. When the number of database connections reaches a certain number, it causes the application to throw an OutOfMemoryException as the garbage collector fails to collect the dead connections.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) - 0 (sast)","name":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)","id":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref - 14846722546022341732 (sast)","name":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The  loads and parses XML using parse, at line 48 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, getInputStream, at line 44 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java. Note that parse is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n","markdown":"The  loads and parses XML using parse, at line 48 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, getInputStream, at line 44 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java. Note that parse is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The  loads and parses XML using parse, at line 48 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, getInputStream, at line 44 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java. Note that parse is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref","id":"Improper Restriction of XXE Ref - 14846722546022341732 (sast)","description":"The  loads and parses XML using parse, at line 48 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java.\n\nThis XML was received earlier from user input, getInputStream, at line 44 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/xxe.java. Note that parse is set to automatically load and replace any DTD entity references in the XML, including references to external files.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Improper Access Control - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Access Control","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Access Control","id":"Improper Access Control - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Cx78f40514-81ff (sca)","name":"Cx78f4051481ff","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The framework Apache Commons Collections before 4.3 is vulnerable to Stack Overflow. The function `add()` in the file `SetUniqueList.java` throws a StackOverflowError when the `add()` method is called with its own list. Please note: the package name was changed from \u0026#34;commons-collections:commons-collections\u0026#34; to \u0026#34;org.apache.commons:commons-collections4\u0026#34; on version 4.0.","markdown":"The framework Apache Commons Collections before 4.3 is vulnerable to Stack Overflow. The function `add()` in the file `SetUniqueList.java` throws a StackOverflowError when the `add()` method is called with its own list. Please note: the package name was changed from \u0026#34;commons-collections:commons-collections\u0026#34; to \u0026#34;org.apache.commons:commons-collections4\u0026#34; on version 4.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The framework Apache Commons Collections before 4.3 is vulnerable to Stack Overflow. The function `add()` in the file `SetUniqueList.java` throws a StackOverflowError when the `add()` method is called with its own list. Please note: the package name was changed from \u0026#34;commons-collections:commons-collections\u0026#34; to \u0026#34;org.apache.commons:commons-collections4\u0026#34; on version 4.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cx78f4051481ff","id":"Cx78f40514-81ff (sca)","description":"The framework Apache Commons Collections before 4.3 is vulnerable to Stack Overflow. The function `add()` in the file `SetUniqueList.java` throws a StackOverflowError when the `add()` method is called with its own list. Please note: the package name was changed from \u0026#34;commons-collections:commons-collections\u0026#34; to \u0026#34;org.apache.commons:commons-collections4\u0026#34; on version 4.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2017-3523 (sca)","name":"Cve20173523","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.40 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.5 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.40 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.5 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.40 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.5 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20173523","id":"CVE-2017-3523 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.40 and earlier. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.5 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H).","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Cx6f651376-312a (sca)","name":"Cx6f651376312a","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"MySQL Connector/J before version 5.1.44 and 6.x is vulnerable to memory leak. When using cached server-side prepared statements, a memory leak occurred as references to opened statements were being kept while the statements were being decached; it happened when either the close() method has been called twice on a statement, or when there were conflicting cache entries for a statement and the older entry had not been closed and removed from the opened statement list.\n","markdown":"MySQL Connector/J before version 5.1.44 and 6.x is vulnerable to memory leak. When using cached server-side prepared statements, a memory leak occurred as references to opened statements were being kept while the statements were being decached; it happened when either the close() method has been called twice on a statement, or when there were conflicting cache entries for a statement and the older entry had not been closed and removed from the opened statement list.\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"MySQL Connector/J before version 5.1.44 and 6.x is vulnerable to memory leak. When using cached server-side prepared statements, a memory leak occurred as references to opened statements were being kept while the statements were being decached; it happened when either the close() method has been called twice on a statement, or when there were conflicting cache entries for a statement and the older entry had not been closed and removed from the opened statement list.\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cx6f651376312a","id":"Cx6f651376-312a (sca)","description":"MySQL Connector/J before version 5.1.44 and 6.x is vulnerable to memory leak. When using cached server-side prepared statements, a memory leak occurred as references to opened statements were being kept while the statements were being decached; it happened when either the close() method has been called twice on a statement, or when there were conflicting cache entries for a statement and the older entry had not been closed and removed from the opened statement list.\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"External Control of File Name or Path - 0 (sast)","name":"External Control of File Name or Path","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"External Control of File Name or Path","id":"External Control of File Name or Path - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2022-45690 (sca)","name":"Cve202245690","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;org.json.JSONTokener.nextValue::JSONTokener.java\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20220320.","markdown":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;org.json.JSONTokener.nextValue::JSONTokener.java\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20220320."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;org.json.JSONTokener.nextValue::JSONTokener.java\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20220320."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202245690","id":"CVE-2022-45690 (sca)","description":"A stack overflow in the \u0026#34;org.json.JSONTokener.nextValue::JSONTokener.java\u0026#34; component of hutool-json allows attackers to cause a Denial of Service (DoS) via crafted JSON or XML data. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20220320.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Absolute Path Traversal - 4635938147065118004 (sast)","name":"Absolute Path Traversal","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Absolute Path Traversal","id":"Absolute Path Traversal - 4635938147065118004 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Cxdb5a1032-eda2 (sca)","name":"Cxdb5a1032eda2","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The package `JSON-java` before 20200518 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service. The function `nextMeta` in the file `XMLTokener.java` runs into an infinite loop as the `JSONTokener.nextMeta()` function returns the same character repeatedly and never advances the Tokener index. Due to this flaw, the availability of the application is affected.","markdown":"The package `JSON-java` before 20200518 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service. The function `nextMeta` in the file `XMLTokener.java` runs into an infinite loop as the `JSONTokener.nextMeta()` function returns the same character repeatedly and never advances the Tokener index. Due to this flaw, the availability of the application is affected."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The package `JSON-java` before 20200518 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service. The function `nextMeta` in the file `XMLTokener.java` runs into an infinite loop as the `JSONTokener.nextMeta()` function returns the same character repeatedly and never advances the Tokener index. Due to this flaw, the availability of the application is affected."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cxdb5a1032eda2","id":"Cxdb5a1032-eda2 (sca)","description":"The package `JSON-java` before 20200518 is vulnerable to Denial Of Service. The function `nextMeta` in the file `XMLTokener.java` runs into an infinite loop as the `JSONTokener.nextMeta()` function returns the same character repeatedly and never advances the Tokener index. Due to this flaw, the availability of the application is affected.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Improper Authorization - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Authorization","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Authorization","id":"Improper Authorization - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Unsafe Reflection - 9006313013203553302 (sast)","name":"Unsafe Reflection","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The input obtained by  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 55 affects the invocation of a reflection in  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 111.\n\nInput is derived from user input, allowing attackers to inject parameters containing potentially devastating values into reflection methods.\n\n","markdown":"The input obtained by  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 55 affects the invocation of a reflection in  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 111.\n\nInput is derived from user input, allowing attackers to inject parameters containing potentially devastating values into reflection methods.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The input obtained by  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 55 affects the invocation of a reflection in  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 111.\n\nInput is derived from user input, allowing attackers to inject parameters containing potentially devastating values into reflection methods.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Unsafe Reflection","id":"Unsafe Reflection - 9006313013203553302 (sast)","description":"The input obtained by  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 55 affects the invocation of a reflection in  in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java at line 111.\n\nInput is derived from user input, allowing attackers to inject parameters containing potentially devastating values into reflection methods.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2015-4852 (sca)","name":"Cve20154852","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The WLS Security component in Oracle WebLogic Server 10.3.6.0, 12.1.2.0, 12.1.3.0, and 12.2.1.0 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object in T3 protocol traffic to TCP port 7001, related to \u0026#34;oracle_common/modules/com.bea.core.apache.commons.collections.jar\u0026#34;. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0. NOTE: the scope of this CVE is limited to the WebLogic Server product.","markdown":"The WLS Security component in Oracle WebLogic Server 10.3.6.0, 12.1.2.0, 12.1.3.0, and 12.2.1.0 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object in T3 protocol traffic to TCP port 7001, related to \u0026#34;oracle_common/modules/com.bea.core.apache.commons.collections.jar\u0026#34;. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0. NOTE: the scope of this CVE is limited to the WebLogic Server product."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The WLS Security component in Oracle WebLogic Server 10.3.6.0, 12.1.2.0, 12.1.3.0, and 12.2.1.0 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object in T3 protocol traffic to TCP port 7001, related to \u0026#34;oracle_common/modules/com.bea.core.apache.commons.collections.jar\u0026#34;. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0. NOTE: the scope of this CVE is limited to the WebLogic Server product."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20154852","id":"CVE-2015-4852 (sca)","description":"The WLS Security component in Oracle WebLogic Server 10.3.6.0, 12.1.2.0, 12.1.3.0, and 12.2.1.0 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object in T3 protocol traffic to TCP port 7001, related to \u0026#34;oracle_common/modules/com.bea.core.apache.commons.collections.jar\u0026#34;. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0. NOTE: the scope of this CVE is limited to the WebLogic Server product.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal') - 0 (sast)","name":"Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal')","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal')","id":"Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal') - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2015-6420 (sca)","name":"Cve20156420","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Serialized-object interfaces in certain Cisco Collaboration and Social Media; Endpoint Clients and Client Software; Network Application, Service, and Acceleration; Network and Content Security Devices; Network Management and Provisioning; Routing and Switching - Enterprise and Service Provider; Unified Computing; Voice and Unified Communications Devices; Video, Streaming, TelePresence, and Transcoding Devices; Wireless; and Cisco Hosted Services products allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0.","markdown":"Serialized-object interfaces in certain Cisco Collaboration and Social Media; Endpoint Clients and Client Software; Network Application, Service, and Acceleration; Network and Content Security Devices; Network Management and Provisioning; Routing and Switching - Enterprise and Service Provider; Unified Computing; Voice and Unified Communications Devices; Video, Streaming, TelePresence, and Transcoding Devices; Wireless; and Cisco Hosted Services products allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Serialized-object interfaces in certain Cisco Collaboration and Social Media; Endpoint Clients and Client Software; Network Application, Service, and Acceleration; Network and Content Security Devices; Network Management and Provisioning; Routing and Switching - Enterprise and Service Provider; Unified Computing; Voice and Unified Communications Devices; Video, Streaming, TelePresence, and Transcoding Devices; Wireless; and Cisco Hosted Services products allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20156420","id":"CVE-2015-6420 (sca)","description":"Serialized-object interfaces in certain Cisco Collaboration and Social Media; Endpoint Clients and Client Software; Network Application, Service, and Acceleration; Network and Content Security Devices; Network Management and Provisioning; Routing and Switching - Enterprise and Service Provider; Unified Computing; Voice and Unified Communications Devices; Video, Streaming, TelePresence, and Transcoding Devices; Wireless; and Cisco Hosted Services products allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2018-1000632 (sca)","name":"Cve20181000632","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"dom4j prior to 2.0.3 and 2.1.x prior to 2.1.1 contains a CWE-91: XML Injection vulnerability in Class: Element. Methods: addElement, addAttribute that can result in an attacker tampering with XML documents through XML injection. This attack appear to be exploitable via an attacker specifying attributes or elements in the XML document. \nTo resolve this issue - upgrade to version 2.0.3 or 2.1.1. Please note: the package name was changed to org.dom4j:dom4j on version 2.0.0.","markdown":"dom4j prior to 2.0.3 and 2.1.x prior to 2.1.1 contains a CWE-91: XML Injection vulnerability in Class: Element. Methods: addElement, addAttribute that can result in an attacker tampering with XML documents through XML injection. This attack appear to be exploitable via an attacker specifying attributes or elements in the XML document. \nTo resolve this issue - upgrade to version 2.0.3 or 2.1.1. Please note: the package name was changed to org.dom4j:dom4j on version 2.0.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"dom4j prior to 2.0.3 and 2.1.x prior to 2.1.1 contains a CWE-91: XML Injection vulnerability in Class: Element. Methods: addElement, addAttribute that can result in an attacker tampering with XML documents through XML injection. This attack appear to be exploitable via an attacker specifying attributes or elements in the XML document. \nTo resolve this issue - upgrade to version 2.0.3 or 2.1.1. Please note: the package name was changed to org.dom4j:dom4j on version 2.0.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20181000632","id":"CVE-2018-1000632 (sca)","description":"dom4j prior to 2.0.3 and 2.1.x prior to 2.1.1 contains a CWE-91: XML Injection vulnerability in Class: Element. Methods: addElement, addAttribute that can result in an attacker tampering with XML documents through XML injection. This attack appear to be exploitable via an attacker specifying attributes or elements in the XML document. \nTo resolve this issue - upgrade to version 2.0.3 or 2.1.1. Please note: the package name was changed to org.dom4j:dom4j on version 2.0.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2020-25638 (sca)","name":"Cve202025638","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"A flaw was found in hibernate-core in versions prior to 5.3.20.Final and from 5.4.0.CR1 to 5.4.23.Final. A SQL injection in the implementation of the JPA Criteria API can permit unsanitized literals when a literal is used in the SQL comments of the query. This flaw could allow an attacker to access unauthorized information or possibly conduct further attacks. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to data confidentiality and integrity.","markdown":"A flaw was found in hibernate-core in versions prior to 5.3.20.Final and from 5.4.0.CR1 to 5.4.23.Final. A SQL injection in the implementation of the JPA Criteria API can permit unsanitized literals when a literal is used in the SQL comments of the query. This flaw could allow an attacker to access unauthorized information or possibly conduct further attacks. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to data confidentiality and integrity."},"fullDescription":{"text":"A flaw was found in hibernate-core in versions prior to 5.3.20.Final and from 5.4.0.CR1 to 5.4.23.Final. A SQL injection in the implementation of the JPA Criteria API can permit unsanitized literals when a literal is used in the SQL comments of the query. This flaw could allow an attacker to access unauthorized information or possibly conduct further attacks. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to data confidentiality and integrity."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202025638","id":"CVE-2020-25638 (sca)","description":"A flaw was found in hibernate-core in versions prior to 5.3.20.Final and from 5.4.0.CR1 to 5.4.23.Final. A SQL injection in the implementation of the JPA Criteria API can permit unsanitized literals when a literal is used in the SQL comments of the query. This flaw could allow an attacker to access unauthorized information or possibly conduct further attacks. The highest threat from this vulnerability is to data confidentiality and integrity.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Missing Authorization - 0 (sast)","name":"Missing Authorization","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Missing Authorization","id":"Missing Authorization - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2022-45689 (sca)","name":"Cve202245689","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"hutool-json was discovered to contain an Out-of-Memory error. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20211205.","markdown":"hutool-json was discovered to contain an Out-of-Memory error. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20211205."},"fullDescription":{"text":"hutool-json was discovered to contain an Out-of-Memory error. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20211205."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve202245689","id":"CVE-2022-45689 (sca)","description":"hutool-json was discovered to contain an Out-of-Memory error. This vulnerability affects \u0026#34;cn.hutool:hutool-json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 5.8.11, and \u0026#34;org.json:json\u0026#34; package versions prior to 20211205.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2018-3258 (sca)","name":"Cve20183258","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.12 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.8 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.12 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.8 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.12 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.8 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20183258","id":"CVE-2018-3258 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.12 and prior. Easily exploitable vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 8.8 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Cx08fcacc9-cb99 (sca)","name":"Cx08fcacc9cb99","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The package `JSON-java` before 20180130 is vulnerable to Denial of service. The method `JSONArray()` in class `JSONArray()` of file `JSONArray.java`, doesn\u0026#39;t check for unclosed array while parsing, causing the application to crash, due to an StackOverflowException. This affects the Availability of the application. ","markdown":"The package `JSON-java` before 20180130 is vulnerable to Denial of service. The method `JSONArray()` in class `JSONArray()` of file `JSONArray.java`, doesn\u0026#39;t check for unclosed array while parsing, causing the application to crash, due to an StackOverflowException. This affects the Availability of the application. "},"fullDescription":{"text":"The package `JSON-java` before 20180130 is vulnerable to Denial of service. The method `JSONArray()` in class `JSONArray()` of file `JSONArray.java`, doesn\u0026#39;t check for unclosed array while parsing, causing the application to crash, due to an StackOverflowException. This affects the Availability of the application. "},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cx08fcacc9cb99","id":"Cx08fcacc9-cb99 (sca)","description":"The package `JSON-java` before 20180130 is vulnerable to Denial of service. The method `JSONArray()` in class `JSONArray()` of file `JSONArray.java`, doesn\u0026#39;t check for unclosed array while parsing, causing the application to crash, due to an StackOverflowException. This affects the Availability of the application. ","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2015-7501 (sca)","name":"Cve20157501","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Red Hat JBoss A-MQ 6.x; BPM Suite (BPMS) 6.x; BRMS 6.x and 5.x; Data Grid (JDG) 6.x; Data Virtualization (JDV) 6.x and 5.x; Enterprise Application Platform 6.x, 5.x, and 4.3.x; Fuse 6.x; Fuse Service Works (FSW) 6.x; Operations Network (JBoss ON) 3.x; Portal 6.x; SOA Platform (SOA-P) 5.x; Web Server (JWS) 3.x; Red Hat OpenShift/xPAAS 3.x; and Red Hat Subscription Asset Manager 1.3 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0.","markdown":"Red Hat JBoss A-MQ 6.x; BPM Suite (BPMS) 6.x; BRMS 6.x and 5.x; Data Grid (JDG) 6.x; Data Virtualization (JDV) 6.x and 5.x; Enterprise Application Platform 6.x, 5.x, and 4.3.x; Fuse 6.x; Fuse Service Works (FSW) 6.x; Operations Network (JBoss ON) 3.x; Portal 6.x; SOA Platform (SOA-P) 5.x; Web Server (JWS) 3.x; Red Hat OpenShift/xPAAS 3.x; and Red Hat Subscription Asset Manager 1.3 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Red Hat JBoss A-MQ 6.x; BPM Suite (BPMS) 6.x; BRMS 6.x and 5.x; Data Grid (JDG) 6.x; Data Virtualization (JDV) 6.x and 5.x; Enterprise Application Platform 6.x, 5.x, and 4.3.x; Fuse 6.x; Fuse Service Works (FSW) 6.x; Operations Network (JBoss ON) 3.x; Portal 6.x; SOA Platform (SOA-P) 5.x; Web Server (JWS) 3.x; Red Hat OpenShift/xPAAS 3.x; and Red Hat Subscription Asset Manager 1.3 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0."},"properties":{"security-severity":"7.0","name":"Cve20157501","id":"CVE-2015-7501 (sca)","description":"Red Hat JBoss A-MQ 6.x; BPM Suite (BPMS) 6.x; BRMS 6.x and 5.x; Data Grid (JDG) 6.x; Data Virtualization (JDV) 6.x and 5.x; Enterprise Application Platform 6.x, 5.x, and 4.3.x; Fuse 6.x; Fuse Service Works (FSW) 6.x; Operations Network (JBoss ON) 3.x; Portal 6.x; SOA Platform (SOA-P) 5.x; Web Server (JWS) 3.x; Red Hat OpenShift/xPAAS 3.x; and Red Hat Subscription Asset Manager 1.3 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary commands via a crafted serialized Java object, related to the Apache Commons Collections (ACC) library. The Java artifact causing the deserialization vulnerability is Apache Commons Collections in versions 3.0 through 3.2.1 and version 4.0.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor - 0 (sast)","name":"Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor","id":"Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor - 0 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CSRF - 6654202269644256546 (sast)","name":"CSRF","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method  at line 58 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java gets a parameter from a user request from \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This parameter value flows through the code and is eventually used to access application state altering functionality. This may enable Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF).\n\n","markdown":"Method  at line 58 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java gets a parameter from a user request from \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This parameter value flows through the code and is eventually used to access application state altering functionality. This may enable Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF).\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method  at line 58 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java gets a parameter from a user request from \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This parameter value flows through the code and is eventually used to access application state altering functionality. This may enable Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF).\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"CSRF","id":"CSRF - 6654202269644256546 (sast)","description":"Method  at line 58 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Install.java gets a parameter from a user request from \u0026#34;\u0026#34;dbname\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This parameter value flows through the code and is eventually used to access application state altering functionality. This may enable Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF).\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Privacy Violation - 12956636075206043460 (sast)","name":"Privacy Violation","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method  at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp sends user information outside the application. This may constitute a Privacy Violation.\n\n","markdown":"Method  at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp sends user information outside the application. This may constitute a Privacy Violation.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method  at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp sends user information outside the application. This may constitute a Privacy Violation.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Privacy Violation","id":"Privacy Violation - 12956636075206043460 (sast)","description":"Method  at line 15 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/login.jsp sends user information outside the application. This may constitute a Privacy Violation.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Parameter Tampering - 7096281910242735216 (sast)","name":"Parameter Tampering","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Method  at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp gets user input from element \u0026#34;\u0026#34;msgid\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This input is later used by the application directly as a parameter in a Create, Read, Update, or Delete (CRUD) operation, without being validated. The application then uses this input in method  to access the database executeQuery, at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp, without any additional server-side filtering or verification. This could allow the user to tamper with the parameter to attempt unauthorized access or manipulate which records are created, read, updated, or deleted.\n\n","markdown":"Method  at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp gets user input from element \u0026#34;\u0026#34;msgid\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This input is later used by the application directly as a parameter in a Create, Read, Update, or Delete (CRUD) operation, without being validated. The application then uses this input in method  to access the database executeQuery, at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp, without any additional server-side filtering or verification. This could allow the user to tamper with the parameter to attempt unauthorized access or manipulate which records are created, read, updated, or deleted.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Method  at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp gets user input from element \u0026#34;\u0026#34;msgid\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This input is later used by the application directly as a parameter in a Create, Read, Update, or Delete (CRUD) operation, without being validated. The application then uses this input in method  to access the database executeQuery, at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp, without any additional server-side filtering or verification. This could allow the user to tamper with the parameter to attempt unauthorized access or manipulate which records are created, read, updated, or deleted.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Parameter Tampering","id":"Parameter Tampering - 7096281910242735216 (sast)","description":"Method  at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp gets user input from element \u0026#34;\u0026#34;msgid\u0026#34;\u0026#34;. This input is later used by the application directly as a parameter in a Create, Read, Update, or Delete (CRUD) operation, without being validated. The application then uses this input in method  to access the database executeQuery, at line 16 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/webapp/vulnerability/DisplayMessage.jsp, without any additional server-side filtering or verification. This could allow the user to tamper with the parameter to attempt unauthorized access or manipulate which records are created, read, updated, or deleted.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Open Redirect - 5854466950125120303 (sast)","name":"Open Redirect","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The potentially tainted value provided by \u0026#34;\u0026#34;url\u0026#34;\u0026#34; in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Open.java at line 36 is used as a destination URL by sendRedirect in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Open.java at line 39, potentially allowing attackers to perform an open redirection.\n\n","markdown":"The potentially tainted value provided by \u0026#34;\u0026#34;url\u0026#34;\u0026#34; in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Open.java at line 36 is used as a destination URL by sendRedirect in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/Open.java a