#39;s  method constructs an XPath query, for navigating an XML document. The XPath query is created with compile, at line 53 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java, using an untrusted string embedded in the expression.  \r\n\r\nThis may enable an attacker to modify the XPath expression, leading to an XPath Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker may be able to inject the modified XPath expression via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;password\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 36 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java. This value then flows through the code to compile, as noted.\n\n","markdown":"The application\u0026#39;s  method constructs an XPath query, for navigating an XML document. The XPath query is created with compile, at line 53 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java, using an untrusted string embedded in the expression.  \r\n\r\nThis may enable an attacker to modify the XPath expression, leading to an XPath Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker may be able to inject the modified XPath expression via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;password\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 36 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java. This value then flows through the code to compile, as noted.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The application\u0026#39;s  method constructs an XPath query, for navigating an XML document. The XPath query is created with compile, at line 53 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java, using an untrusted string embedded in the expression.  \r\n\r\nThis may enable an attacker to modify the XPath expression, leading to an XPath Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker may be able to inject the modified XPath expression via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;password\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 36 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java. This value then flows through the code to compile, as noted.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"XPath Injection","id":"XPath Injection - 7757101306809734090 (sast)","description":"The application\u0026#39;s  method constructs an XPath query, for navigating an XML document. The XPath query is created with compile, at line 53 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java, using an untrusted string embedded in the expression.  \r\n\r\nThis may enable an attacker to modify the XPath expression, leading to an XPath Injection attack.\n\nThe attacker may be able to inject the modified XPath expression via user input, \u0026#34;\u0026#34;password\u0026#34;\u0026#34;, which is retrieved by the application in the  method, at line 36 of /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/controller/XPathQuery.java. This value then flows through the code to compile, as noted.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Plaintext Storage of a Password - 2469627820054694864 (sast)","name":"Plaintext Storage of a Password","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The password 26 did not used a secure scheme to store the password - this may allow attackers to retrieve it, and use it to access authenticated resources. \n\n","markdown":"The password 26 did not used a secure scheme to store the password - this may allow attackers to retrieve it, and use it to access authenticated resources. \n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"The password 26 did not used a secure scheme to store the password - this may allow attackers to retrieve it, and use it to access authenticated resources. \n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Plaintext Storage of a Password","id":"Plaintext Storage of a Password - 2469627820054694864 (sast)","description":"The password 26 did not used a secure scheme to store the password - this may allow attackers to retrieve it, and use it to access authenticated resources. \n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2022-21363 (sca)","name":"Cve202221363","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.27 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.1 Base Score 6.6 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.27 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.1 Base Score 6.6 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.27 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.1 Base Score 6.6 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Cve202221363","id":"CVE-2022-21363 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.27 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.1 Base Score 6.6 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2020-2934 (sca)","name":"Cve20202934","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.19 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a partial denial of service (partial DOS) of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.0 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.19 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a partial denial of service (partial DOS) of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.0 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.19 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a partial denial of service (partial DOS) of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.0 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Cve20202934","id":"CVE-2020-2934 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.19 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a partial denial of service (partial DOS) of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 5.0 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:L/A:L).","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2020-2875 (sca)","name":"Cve20202875","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.14 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.7 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.14 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.7 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.14 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.7 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Cve20202875","id":"CVE-2020-2875 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.14 and prior and 5.1.48 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows unauthenticated attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker and while the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 4.7 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:R/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N).","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Use of Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm - 15434822379289186737 (sast)","name":"Use of Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"In , the application protects sensitive data using a cryptographic algorithm, getInstance, that is considered weak or even trivially broken, in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/model/HashMe.java at line 16.\n\n","markdown":"In , the application protects sensitive data using a cryptographic algorithm, getInstance, that is considered weak or even trivially broken, in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/model/HashMe.java at line 16.\n\n"},"fullDescription":{"text":"In , the application protects sensitive data using a cryptographic algorithm, getInstance, that is considered weak or even trivially broken, in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/model/HashMe.java at line 16.\n\n"},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Use of Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm","id":"Use of Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm - 15434822379289186737 (sast)","description":"In , the application protects sensitive data using a cryptographic algorithm, getInstance, that is considered weak or even trivially broken, in /AllScanTypes/src/main/java/org/cysecurity/cspf/jvl/model/HashMe.java at line 16.\n\n","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"CVE-2019-2692 (sca)","name":"Cve20192692","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.15 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Connectors executes to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.3 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.15 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Connectors executes to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.3 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.15 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Connectors executes to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.3 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Cve20192692","id":"CVE-2019-2692 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 8.0.15 and prior. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with logon to the infrastructure where MySQL Connectors executes to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks require human interaction from a person other than the attacker. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in takeover of MySQL Connectors. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.3 (Confidentiality, Integrity and Availability impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:H/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2021-2471 (sca)","name":"Cve20212471","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). This vulnerability affects versions through 8.0.26. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Connectors.","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). This vulnerability affects versions through 8.0.26. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Connectors."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). This vulnerability affects versions through 8.0.26. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Connectors."},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Cve20212471","id":"CVE-2021-2471 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors product of Oracle MySQL (component: Connector/J). This vulnerability affects versions through 8.0.26. Difficult to exploit vulnerability allows high privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized access to critical data or complete access to all MySQL Connectors accessible data and unauthorized ability to cause a hang or frequently repeatable crash (complete DOS) of MySQL Connectors.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"CVE-2017-3586 (sca)","name":"Cve20173586","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.41 and earlier. Easily \u0026#34;exploitable\u0026#34; vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.4 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N).","markdown":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.41 and earlier. Easily \u0026#34;exploitable\u0026#34; vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.4 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N)."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.41 and earlier. Easily \u0026#34;exploitable\u0026#34; vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Successful attacks of this vulnerability can result in unauthorized update, insert or delete access to some of MySQL Connectors accessible data as well as unauthorized read access to a subset of MySQL Connectors accessible data. CVSS 3.0 Base Score 6.4 (Confidentiality and Integrity impacts). CVSS Vector: (CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:L/A:N)."},"properties":{"security-severity":"4.0","name":"Cve20173586","id":"CVE-2017-3586 (sca)","description":"Vulnerability in the MySQL Connectors component of Oracle MySQL (subcomponent: Connector/J). Supported versions that are affected are 5.1.41 and earlier. Easily \u0026#34;exploitable\u0026#34; vulnerability allows low privileged attacker with network access via multiple protocols to compromise MySQL Connectors. While the vulnerability is in MySQL Connectors, attacks may significantly impact additional products. Suc